{"article_id":"p0eZ8Zc3wymZ4LhK","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Obama Calls For Small Package Of Cuts , Tax Changes","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"To Head Off 'Sequester '","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"( We updated the top of this post at 1:30 p.m . ET . )","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"Looking to head off deep , automatic spending cuts","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"set to kick in on March 1 ,","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"President Obama on Tuesday afternoon said","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"to avoid the negative economic effects","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"that come with `` political disfunction ,","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"'' Congress should move quickly to pass `` a smaller package of spending cuts and tax reforms ''","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"that wo n't hurt the economy .","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"Acknowledging","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"that Congress likely wo n't be able to pass a `` full budget '' by March 1","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"and avoid the so-called sequester","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"that would bring sharp reductions in spending on defense and other programs ,","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"Obama pushed for a temporary plan","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"that would give lawmakers another few months","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"to negotiate on a larger deficit reduction package .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"The president also used an early afternoon appearance in the White House briefing room","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"to push for a long-term deal","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"that includes a `` balanced mix of spending cuts and more tax reform . ''","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"He also said","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"that `` deals","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"I put forward '' in recent negotiations","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"- such as changing the way","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"entitlement programs are adjusted for the cost of living -","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"`` are still on the table . ''","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"Before the president 's statement , House Speaker John Boehner , R-Ohio , released a statement","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"saying","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"that `` Americans do not support replacing real spending cuts with more tax increases . ''","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"President Obama will `` call on Congress to act","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"to avoid the sequester","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"and reduce the deficit in a balanced way . ''","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"the White House says .","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"Officials tell the White House press corps","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"that the president `` will call on Congress to pass a smaller package of spending cuts and tax reforms","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"to avoid the economically harmful consequences of the sequester for a few months . ''","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"He 's scheduled to issue that call around 1:15 p.m . ET . `` Congress created the sequester as a forcing mechanism .","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"Across-the-board cuts would only take effect","depth":14},{"id":39,"text":"if lawmakers failed to agree on a deficit reduction plan .","depth":14},{"id":40,"text":"These cuts were designed","depth":15},{"id":41,"text":"to be so draconian","depth":15},{"id":42,"text":"that Congress would have no choice","depth":15},{"id":43,"text":"but to cut the deficit .","depth":15},{"id":44,"text":"`` That 's not how it worked out .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"``","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"Congress failed to reach an agreement ,","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"and now the sequester is looming .","depth":14},{"id":48,"text":"The White House believes","depth":15},{"id":49,"text":"it 's already hurting economic growth .","depth":15},{"id":50,"text":"`` So today , President Obama will call on Congress to pass a small package of spending cuts and tax changes .","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"`` A White House official says","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"this is intended to give more time","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"to reach a solution","depth":15},{"id":54,"text":"that permanently avoids the sequester","depth":16},{"id":55,"text":"and significantly reduces the deficit . ''","depth":16},{"id":56,"text":"Update at 1:05 p. m. ET .","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"New Deficit Numbers And A Warning From The CBO :","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"There 's a good chance","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"the president will talk about this -","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"the Congressional Budget Office just reported","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"that :","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"`` Economic growth will remain slow this year ,","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"CBO anticipates ,","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"as gradual improvement in many of the forces","depth":14},{"id":65,"text":"that drive the economy","depth":14},{"id":66,"text":"is offset by the effects of budgetary changes","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"that are scheduled to occur under current law . ...","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"`` f the current laws","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"that govern federal taxes and spending","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"do not change ,","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"the budget deficit will shrink this year to $ 845 billion , or 5.3 percent of gross domestic product","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"( GDP ) ,","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"its smallest size since 2008 .","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"In CBO 's baseline projections , deficits continue to shrink over the next few years ,","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"falling to 2.4 percent of GDP by 2015 . ''","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"We 've added an audio player","depth":3},{"id":77,"text":"if you wish to hear NPR 's coverage .","depth":4},{"id":78,"text":"It should be at the top of the post .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":157,"left":80,"right":156,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":80,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":153,"right":155,"relation":"elaboration","nuc